class Solution {
    public String breakPalindrome(String palindrome) {
        char[] chars = palindrome.toCharArray();
        int n = chars.length;
        for (int i = 0; i < n / 2; i++) {
            if (chars[i] != 'a') {
                chars[i] = 'a';
                return new String(chars);
            }
        }
        chars[n - 1] = 'b';
        return n == 1 ? "" : new String(chars);
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N)
space complexity: O(N)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates over the first half of the palindrome, replacing the first non-'a' character with 'a'. If all characters in the first half are 'a', it changes the last character to 'b'. This approach ensures the resulting string is the lexicographically smallest non-palindrome. 
